Daily Habits 

1. Sketch: Sketching or painting designs in a notebook gets my creative juices flowing. This simple exercise helps me get in the zone and generates the energy I need to be creative, so I try to work this practice in daily.

2. Experiment: Part of selling my work requires me to produce many pieces with the same design. To break up the monotony and keep me sane, I try to work daily on at least one piece that is just for fun and something that excites me.

3. Clean: This one has taken possibly the most practice. When you’re just one person and your to make list is long, it’s hard to give up precious hours to clean a space you know you will just make messy again the following day. However, it’s a game changer to walk into a tidy studio in the morning. I’m much more productive and the mess doesn’t start to accumulate too badly if I keep up with it.

4. Move: Some of my best ideas have come to me while exercising. It is obviously great for your overall health, but as a creator it helps me step away and destress. When I’m taking care of myself I’m more likely to bring my best into my work as well. 

Just a peek into my world, what are some of your daily habits you couldn’t live without?
